@startuml digital_key_and_signal_bars_to_pak_proximity_latency_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Digital Key And Signal Bars To PAK Proximity Latency Signal Flow\n(digital-key + TMU signal bars + vehicle state -> PAK proximity and sync-latency publication)

participant "Digital-key bus" as DKey #F4F7FB
participant "TMU service bus" as TMU #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state bus" as Veh #FCE8FF
participant "PAK\nphone-as-key owner" as PAK #E8F7E8
participant "PAK state bus" as PakBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\naccess readers" as Obs #FFF4CC

== PAK Inputs ==

DKey -> PAK : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nDKeyState / AuthMode
TMU -> PAK : frmTmuServiceStateMsg\nSignalBars
Veh -> PAK : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\ngDriveState
activate PAK
PAK -> PAK : dkey/tmu/vehicle staleness lease checks
PAK -> PAK : if stale then clear\ndkey auth or signal bars
PAK -> PAK : ProximityState = 1 when\nSignalBars >= 2
PAK -> PAK : ProximityState = 2 when\nSignalBars >= 4 and driveState == 0
PAK -> PAK : SyncLatency = clamp(200 - bars*30, 20..255)
note right of PAK
Representative gating inputs
- DKeyState
- AuthMode
- SignalBars
- gDriveState
end note

== PAK Publish ==

PAK -> PakBus : frmPhoneAsKeyStateMsg\nPaakState / AuthLevel /\nProximityState / SyncLatency
note right of PAK
Representative outputs
- PaakState
- AuthLevel
- ProximityState
- SyncLatency
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

PakBus -> Obs : access visibility /\nPAAK and keyless readers
deactivate PAK

note over DKey, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Digital-key state, TMU signal bars, and vehicle state reach PAK
2. PAK checks freshness and access posture
3. PAK derives proximity state and sync latency
4. PAK publishes phone-as-key state for downstream access readers
end note

@enduml
